sentences: The musicians of the RMS Titanic all perished when the ship sank in 1912.

sentences: Roger Marie Bricoux (1 June 1891 – 15 April 1912) was a French cellist on the RMS Titanic on its maiden voyage.
Roger Bricoux (in French) was born on 1 June 1891 in rue de Donzy, Cosne-sur-Loire, France.
After studying at the Paris Conservatory, he moved to England in 1910 to join the orchestra in the Grand Central Hotel in Leeds.
At the end of 1911, he moved to Lille, France, lived at 5 Place du Lion d'Or, and played in various locations throughout the city.
He boarded the Titanic  on Wednesday 10 April 1912 in Southampton, UK.
His ticket number was 250654, the ticket for all the members of Wallace Hartley's orchestra.
Bricoux was 20 years old when he died.
In 1913, after his apparent disappearance, he was declared a "deserter" by the French army.
It was not until 2000 that he was eventually officially registered as dead in France, mainly due to the efforts of the Association Française du Titanic.
On 2 November 2000, the same association unveiled a memorial plaque to Bricoux in Cosne-Cours-sur-Loire.
